Hey @AdityaJ2305,
I might be wrong, but I think defining maxValue function as a global function outside component might be a better idea, as we would still be able to avoid unnecessary function recreation, without having to cache the function.
```
const maxValue = useMemo(() => {
    switch (selected.unit) {
      case "days":
        return 31;
      case "weeks":
        return 12;
      case "months":
        return 36;
      case "years":
        return 60;
      default:
        return 31;
    }
  }, [selected.unit]);
  ```
  Please correct me if I am wrong.
 
 Regards
 Aman Sharma
